text: Jewett Norris Library, also known as Grundy County Jewett Norris Library, is a historic library building located at Trenton, Grundy County, Missouri. It was built in 1891, and is a 2 1/2-story, Romanesque Revival style red brick and limestone building. It has a high stone base and broad stone steps leading to a porch with heavy, round stone arches. (includes 4 photographs from 1984) It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1984. ==References== ==External links== *Library website Category:Libraries on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Romanesque Revival architecture in Missouri Category:Library buildings completed in 1891 Category:Buildings and structures in Grundy County, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Grundy County, Missouri
